WEBVTT

00:00.171 --> 00:01.001
PREVIOUSLY ON REAPER...

00:01.001 --> 00:03.034
IS THIS A CARJACKING?
ARE YOU CARJACKING ME?

00:03.034 --> 00:03.674
I'M THE DEVIL.

00:03.674 --> 00:05.076
PARENTS SOLD MY SOUL
TO THE DEVIL.

00:05.076 --> 00:06.737
NOW I'M A BOUNTY HUNTER
FOR HELL.

00:06.737 --> 00:07.338
YOU GONNA TELL ANDI?

00:07.338 --> 00:10.541
NO, I'M NOT GONNA TELL ANDI.
IF SHE KNOWS,
SHE'LL THINK I'M A FREAK.

00:10.541 --> 00:11.542
SHE'LL NEVER
GO OUT WITH ME.

00:11.542 --> 00:13.384
WHATEVER, MAN.
SHE WAS ALL UP
IN YOUR GRILL PIECE,

00:13.384 --> 00:14.445
AND YOU TOLD HER
TO TAKE A HIKE.

00:14.445 --> 00:15.486
AND HOW AM I SUPPOSED
TO CAPTURE HIM?

00:15.486 --> 00:18.219
Devil: THIS WILL HELP--
A VESSEL, HANDCRAFTED IN
THE BOWELS OF PERDITION

00:18.219 --> 00:20.151
BY THE INIQUITOUS
AND THE VILE.

00:20.151 --> 00:23.154
YOU PUT A SOUL IN HELL.
HOW DOES THAT FEEL, HUH?

00:23.154 --> 00:25.356
THAT'S PURE,
UNADULTERATED SATISFACTION.

00:25.356 --> 00:29.100
ALL THE MONEY AND TAIL
IN THE WORLD CAN'T COMPARE.

00:29.100 --> 00:31.802
[BECAUSE I'M AWESOME
BY THE DOLLYROTS PLAYING]

00:31.802 --> 00:35.035
♪ UH-HUH ♪

00:35.536 --> 00:38.109
♪ YOU SAY I'M GIFTED... ♪

00:38.109 --> 00:40.111
[SIGHS]

00:40.111 --> 00:42.243
UNH!

00:44.044 --> 00:46.477
[KEYS JINGLING]

00:47.448 --> 00:49.220
[CAR ALARM BEEPS]

00:50.551 --> 00:54.355
♪ I ALWAYS TELL YOU
HOW SMART YOU ARE ♪

00:54.355 --> 00:54.785
WHAT?

00:54.785 --> 00:57.057
♪ IT'S 'CAUSE MY BRAIN
IS REALLY SUPER-SIZED ♪

00:57.057 --> 01:01.732
♪ YOU'RE AN ACADEMIC
SUPERSTAR ♪

01:01.732 --> 01:03.164
WHA--

01:03.164 --> 01:07.468
♪ I'M A LEADER,
I'M A WINNER ♪

01:07.468 --> 01:09.400
MOM? DAD?

01:09.400 --> 01:11.802
I NEED A RIDE!

01:16.147 --> 01:18.509
Sam: THANKS. [GRUNTS]

01:19.180 --> 01:20.851
THAT'S 14 EVEN.

01:20.851 --> 01:23.514
OK.

01:27.218 --> 01:27.818
YOU BEING CUTE?

01:27.818 --> 01:32.493
UH, NO, I--
I SWEAR THE MONEY
WAS JUST IN MY HAND...

01:32.493 --> 01:35.726
ALONG WITH MY WALLET.

01:35.726 --> 01:38.129
UM...

01:38.129 --> 01:41.202
BEN! HEY, WOULD YOU--
HOLD ON ONE SECOND, OK?

01:41.202 --> 01:42.503
BEN! BEN, HEY.

01:42.503 --> 01:43.604
DUDE, I NEED SOME CASH.

01:43.604 --> 01:47.178
CAN I BORROW SOME, UH...
SOME...REALLY?

01:47.178 --> 01:50.581
WHAT ARE YOU D--
I KNOW YOU CAN HEAR ME!

01:52.243 --> 01:55.115
SO, WHAT, JUST DISAPPEARED
OUT OF YOUR HAND?

01:55.115 --> 01:57.848
YEAH, MONEY, WALLET, KEYS.
IT WAS NOT A GOOD MORNING.

01:57.848 --> 02:00.691
OH, WAIT.
ARE THESE YOURS?

02:00.691 --> 02:01.652
WHERE'D YOU FIND THOSE?

02:01.652 --> 02:03.794
THEY WERE IN MY POCKET
LIKE 20 MINUTES AGO.

02:03.794 --> 02:05.296
I HAVE NO IDEA
HOW IT GOT THERE.

02:05.296 --> 02:07.658
I DO. IT'S MY
DEVIL POWER KICKING IN.

02:07.658 --> 02:09.560
WAIT, TO MAKE STUFF
DISAPPEAR?

02:09.560 --> 02:12.763
YEAH, IT'S SUPPOSED TO
POINT ME IN THE DIRECTION
OF AN ESCAPED SOUL FROM HELL

02:12.763 --> 02:14.565
SO I CAN HUNT THEM DOWN
AND SEND THEM BACK.

02:14.565 --> 02:17.468
HEY, HEY. GUYS.
LITTLE HELP?

02:17.468 --> 02:18.709
IT'S THE PAINT MIXER RODEO.

02:18.709 --> 02:22.643
THAT'S ONE ANGRY LOOKING BULL.
YOU SURE YOU'RE
READY FOR THIS?

02:22.643 --> 02:23.774
[GRUNTING]

02:23.774 --> 02:26.547
THIS IS NOT MY FIRST TIME
AT THE RODEO, SON.

02:26.547 --> 02:27.878
CLOCK READY.

02:27.878 --> 02:29.520
THANK YOU, BEN.

02:29.520 --> 02:31.582
GUYS, READY?

02:35.586 --> 02:36.887
RELEASE THE BULL.

02:36.887 --> 02:38.529
OK! GAH!

02:38.529 --> 02:40.160
WHOA HO HO!

02:40.160 --> 02:41.732
GRAVITY MY FOOT!

02:41.732 --> 02:42.733
Ben: WHOO HOO!

02:42.733 --> 02:44.435
YEE-HAW!
WHOO HOO!

02:44.435 --> 02:47.868
[ALL LAUGHING AND SHOUTING]

02:47.868 --> 02:49.169
AAH!

02:49.169 --> 02:50.801
WHOA.

02:50.801 --> 02:52.773
WHOA!

02:54.345 --> 02:56.307
AHH, HA HA HA.

02:56.307 --> 02:59.350
HA HA HA HA HA!

02:59.350 --> 03:00.311
Sock: UH...

03:00.311 --> 03:03.284
OW, NOT THE CROTCH.
NOT THE CROTCH.

03:05.786 --> 03:07.458
SAM...

03:07.458 --> 03:09.590
HUH?
[SOCK CHUCKLES]

03:09.590 --> 03:10.961
I FOUND YOUR WALLET.

03:10.961 --> 03:13.724
Sock: THAT IS AWESOME!

03:32.683 --> 03:34.315
HI, CAN I HELP YOU?

03:34.315 --> 03:35.486
YEAH, HOW MUCH IS THIS?

03:35.486 --> 03:37.548
UM, LET ME SEE.

03:37.548 --> 03:38.719
AAH!

03:38.719 --> 03:40.321
AAH! AAH!

03:40.321 --> 03:43.394
WHA--[PANTING]

03:44.224 --> 03:47.328
I'LL JUST ASK
SOMEONE ELSE.

03:48.799 --> 03:51.462
[PANTING]

03:51.862 --> 03:52.563
WAS THAT YOU?

03:52.563 --> 03:56.307
I JUST--THE DEVIL'S TOTALLY
MESSING WITH MY HEAD.

03:56.307 --> 03:57.908
HEH HEH.
YOU SEE THAT GUY?

03:57.908 --> 03:58.469
YEAH.

03:58.469 --> 04:00.571
I JUST HAD THIS
REALLY WEIRD VISION
THAT HE STABBED ME.

04:00.571 --> 04:03.974
I JUST HAD THIS
REALLY WEIRD CUPCAKE,
SO I GUESS WE'RE EVEN.

04:03.974 --> 04:05.616
UH, COME ON, LET'S GO.

04:05.616 --> 04:06.317
WHERE ARE WE GOING?

04:06.317 --> 04:08.919
NEW DEVIL BOX ARRIVED
RIGHT IN THE MIDDLE
OF THE BACK ROOM.

04:08.919 --> 04:09.980
SCARED THE CRAP
OUT OF BEN.

04:09.980 --> 04:11.782
WHAT ABOUT ME? I JUST
THOUGHT I GOT STABBED.

04:11.782 --> 04:12.623
YOU KNOW HOW SCARY
THAT IS?

04:12.623 --> 04:14.855
YEAH, ALL RIGHT.
COME ON, HERE.
HOP ON. LET'S GO.

04:14.855 --> 04:17.828
COME ON, PIGGYBACK.
IT'LL CHEER YOU UP.
LET'S GO.

04:17.828 --> 04:19.390
COME ON! COME ON!

04:19.390 --> 04:20.861
EH...NO. I'M GOOD.

04:20.861 --> 04:23.263
YEAH, YOU'RE A LITTLE BIG
FOR THAT NOW, AREN'T YA?

04:23.263 --> 04:27.498
JUST SO YOU KNOW,
I WOULD HAVE PIGGYBACKED
YOU RIGHT BACK THERE.

04:28.439 --> 04:30.270
Sock: I WONDER WHAT'S
IN THE BOX THIS TIME.

04:30.270 --> 04:33.374
YOU KNOW, WE MIGHT
AS WELL JUST OPEN IT
AND GET IT OVER WITH.

04:33.374 --> 04:36.307
[BOX SNARLS]
OOH!
OH!

04:36.307 --> 04:38.679
[RATTLES]

04:38.679 --> 04:39.910
SAM, YOUR BOX
WAS MOVING.

04:39.910 --> 04:40.851
YEAH, YEAH, I KNOW.

04:40.851 --> 04:41.882
IT SOUNDS
LIKE IT'S ALIVE.

04:41.882 --> 04:44.885
LIKE THERE'S A LITTLE TINY
DEMON MONSTER TRYING
TO SCRATCH ITS WAY OUT.

04:44.885 --> 04:47.518
THAT WOULD BE AWESOME.
CAN WE OPEN IT?

04:47.518 --> 04:48.619
Andi: HEY, GUYS.

04:48.619 --> 04:49.960
Sam: YEAH, YEAH, HI.

04:49.960 --> 04:52.493
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
YOU LOOK GUILTY.

04:52.493 --> 04:55.326
NO GUILTIER THAN USUAL.
HEH HEH.
NO, NO.

04:55.326 --> 04:55.896
WHAT'S GOING ON?

04:55.896 --> 04:57.368
I'M GOOD.
LISTEN, I NEED
TO TALK TO YOU.

04:57.368 --> 04:59.970
YEAH, YEAH, LET'S--
LET'S TAKE A WALK.
YOU WANNA--

04:59.970 --> 05:01.071
OK. YEAH, YEAH.
ALL RIGHT.

05:01.071 --> 05:04.875
UNIVERSITY OF IDAHO,
FLAMING LIPS CONCERT,

05:04.875 --> 05:06.507
THIS WEEKEND.

05:06.507 --> 05:07.608
SOUNDS GREAT.
YOU GOING?

05:07.608 --> 05:09.039
YEAH. MY COUSIN'S
A STUDENT THERE,

05:09.039 --> 05:10.841
SO HE SAID
HE CAN GET US TICKETS.

05:10.841 --> 05:12.413
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

05:12.413 --> 05:14.515
US, AS IN ME?

05:14.515 --> 05:15.916
YEAH!
OH, GOOD, YEAH.

05:15.916 --> 05:16.487
YOU KNOW, ALL OF US.

05:16.487 --> 05:18.849
BEN, SOCK, JOSIE.
I MEAN, IT'S A 7-HOUR DRIVE,

05:18.849 --> 05:20.991
BUT WE CAN JUST
TAKE TURNS AT THE WHEEL.

05:20.991 --> 05:21.592
RIGHT.

05:21.592 --> 05:23.323
I GUESS, YOU KNOW,
WE NEED A PLACE
TO SPEND THE NIGHT.

05:23.323 --> 05:25.956
UM, SOCK.
SOCK'S UNCLE HAS A VAN.
WE COULD CRASH THERE.

05:25.956 --> 05:26.897
PERFECT!
YEAH.

05:26.897 --> 05:29.760
OK, GREAT.
WE'LL JUST HAVE
A VAN SLUMBER PARTY THEN.

05:29.760 --> 05:32.032
OH, BUT YOU SHOULD KNOW...
I SNORE.

05:32.032 --> 05:34.935
EXTREMELY LOUD,
LIKE A 50-YEAR-OLD MAN.

05:34.935 --> 05:36.767
HEH. NICE.

05:36.767 --> 05:38.038
HA HA.
IT'S REALLY ATTRACTIVE.

05:38.038 --> 05:40.040
WELL, I MYSELF
AM A DROOLER, SO...

05:40.040 --> 05:41.972
OH! FANTASTIC THEN.
PERFECT.

05:41.972 --> 05:44.715
I MEAN, THIS IS GONNA BE
SO MUCH FUN, RIGHT?

05:44.715 --> 05:47.077
I MEAN, JUST THE 5 OF US
GOING AWAY FOR THE WEEKEND.

05:47.077 --> 05:50.020
WE'LL HAVE BED HEAD
TOGETHER.
IT'S GONNA BE--

05:50.020 --> 05:51.782
MY OFFICE NOW.

05:51.782 --> 05:53.754
AND BRING THE MORONS.

05:53.754 --> 05:56.727
UM...OK.

05:56.727 --> 05:57.958
[PEN CLICKING]

05:57.958 --> 05:58.859
[EXHALES]

05:58.859 --> 06:01.532
CAN YOU TELL ME
ABOUT THIS CAN
OF WASTED PAINT?

06:01.532 --> 06:03.464
IT'S LEAKING
ONTO YOUR DESK.

06:03.464 --> 06:04.695
[GASPS]

06:04.695 --> 06:07.367
I FOUND 6 OTHERS
JUST LIKE IT

06:07.367 --> 06:08.839
IN THE DUMPSTER.

06:08.839 --> 06:10.801
SEEMS THE RODEO
IS BACK IN TOWN.

06:10.801 --> 06:12.943
WHAT CAN I SAY, TED?
YOU CAN'T FENCE THIS COWBOY IN.

06:12.943 --> 06:17.147
WELL, CONGRATULATIONS.
YOU HAVE JUST INCURRED
THE WRATH OF TED.

06:17.147 --> 06:19.049
HOLD ON A SECOND.
I WASN'T EVEN THERE.

06:19.049 --> 06:19.910
WHY AM I BEING PUNISHED?

06:19.910 --> 06:22.052
BECAUSE, ANDI,
IF YOU'RE NOT
PART OF THE SOLUTION,

06:22.052 --> 06:23.614
THEN YOU'RE
PART OF THE PROBLEM.

06:23.614 --> 06:27.818
THERE WILL BE
NO MORE TALKING OF
A SOCIAL NATURE AT WORK.

06:27.818 --> 06:29.420
ANY OF YOU.

06:29.420 --> 06:31.722
WOW.
HOLD ON. WHY?

06:31.722 --> 06:32.523
WHY, SAM?

06:32.523 --> 06:35.796
BECAUSE THE WORKBENCH
IS MY WORLD,

06:35.796 --> 06:38.929
AND I WILL NOT LET YOUR
CHAOS DESTROY THIS WORLD.

06:38.929 --> 06:41.632
SO THAT MEANS THERE WILL
BE NO MORE TALKING,

06:41.632 --> 06:43.874
CHIT-CHATTING,
AND/OR YARN SPINNING.

06:43.874 --> 06:47.478
I'M SORRY, TED.
I'M NOT FEELIN' THIS PLAN.
WHAT ELSE YOU GOT?

06:47.478 --> 06:49.910
OH, I GOT
WEEKEND SHIFTS,

06:49.910 --> 06:52.082
NIGHT SHIFTS,
HOLIDAY HOURS.

06:52.082 --> 06:56.487
I HAVE THE POWER
TO DESTROY
YOUR SOCIAL LIVES

06:56.487 --> 07:00.491
UNTIL YOU BEG ME...

07:00.491 --> 07:02.152
TO FIRE YOU.

07:02.152 --> 07:04.595
SO GOOD DAY, SIR.

07:04.955 --> 07:06.957
YOU KNOW WHAT, SAM?
HUH?

07:06.957 --> 07:10.631
I THINK THAT I AM
OUTRAGED RIGHT NOW.

07:10.631 --> 07:11.762
GOOD TO KNOW, YEAH.

07:11.762 --> 07:13.003
CAN YOU HELP ME, PLEASE?

07:13.003 --> 07:14.064
[WHIMPERS]

07:14.064 --> 07:15.536
I CA--I CAN'T, SAM.

07:15.536 --> 07:16.907
I'M TOO DISGRUNTLED,
ALL RIGHT?

07:16.907 --> 07:19.940
I MEAN, GIVE ME A BREAK.
NO TALKING AT WORK?

07:19.940 --> 07:23.514
I MEAN, WHAT'S NEXT?
TAKE AWAY THE AIR
THAT I BREATHE?

07:23.514 --> 07:27.618
TAKE AWAY THE BEER
THAT I'M ABOUT
TO DRINK ON MY BREAK?

07:27.618 --> 07:28.048
COME ON.

07:28.048 --> 07:29.720
WHAT? YOU GOT BEER?
WHERE'D YOU GET BEER?

07:29.720 --> 07:32.052
I ACTUALLY HIT
THE DIET ICED TEA BUTTON
THE VENDING MACHINE,

07:32.052 --> 07:34.955
AND THIS JUST CAME OUT.
I THINK MAYBE
IT'S A SIGN.

07:34.955 --> 07:36.957
WANT HALF?
YES, I WANT HALF.

07:36.957 --> 07:39.029
YEAH?
I LOVE YOU RIGHT NOW.

07:39.029 --> 07:40.030
HAVE A SEAT, BRO.

07:40.030 --> 07:41.131
YOU KNOW WHAT?
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT, MAN.

07:41.131 --> 07:43.664
IT'LL ALL BLOW OVER
IT'S TED. IT'S A CYCLE.

07:43.664 --> 07:44.735
HE ALWAYS DOES THIS.

07:44.735 --> 07:45.235
I'M NOT LIKE YOU, MAN.

07:45.235 --> 07:46.897
I CAN'T JUST SIT BACK
AND LET TED
WALK ALL OVER ME.

07:46.897 --> 07:49.670
I DON'T--WHAT?
I DON'T LET TED
WALK ALL OVER ME.

07:49.670 --> 07:50.571
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

07:50.571 --> 07:53.544
SURE, YOU DO. AND IT'S
OK BECAUSE BETA MALES
ARE IN RIGHT NOW.

07:53.544 --> 07:54.645
OK? CHICKS DIG IT.

07:54.645 --> 07:55.776
GOOD TO KNOW.
GOOD TO KNOW.

07:55.776 --> 07:59.149
I REFUSE TO ACCEPT
TED'S POWER OVER ME.

07:59.149 --> 08:00.981
WE HAVE RIGHTS, OK?

08:00.981 --> 08:03.984
WE ARE NOT MACHINES.
WE ARE NOT ROBOTS.

08:03.984 --> 08:06.857
BE COOLER
IF WE WERE ROBOTS.

08:06.857 --> 08:07.718
YEAH.

08:07.718 --> 08:09.489
YOU KNOW WHO I'D BE
IF I WAS A ROBOT?

08:09.489 --> 08:11.792
WHO?
THE HOT CHICK
FROM TERMINATOR 3.

08:11.792 --> 08:14.164
FIRST I WOULD
TEAR THIS BUILDING DOWN
BRICK BY BRICK,

08:14.164 --> 08:16.496
THEN I WOULD GO HOME,
LOCK MYSELF
IN THE BATHROOM,

08:16.496 --> 08:18.098
AND STARE AT MY BOOBS
FOR AS LONG AS I WANTED.

08:18.098 --> 08:19.970
YEAH.
WHICH WOULD
BE A LONG TIME.

08:19.970 --> 08:22.603
AND THEN TED WOULD HAVE
NO POWER OVER YOU.

08:22.603 --> 08:24.104
TESTIFY.

08:30.641 --> 08:33.013
[CAN CLANKS]

08:35.886 --> 08:36.787
OH, SAM.

08:36.787 --> 08:39.019
LIFE'S TOO SHORT
TO DRINK DOMESTIC.

08:39.019 --> 08:40.290
WHAT'S THAT?

08:40.290 --> 08:42.192
WHAT?

08:42.923 --> 08:45.896
I COULD GO FOR ONE
OF THESE APPLES. YOU?

08:45.896 --> 08:46.897
[SIGHS]

08:46.897 --> 08:49.760
Sam: WHAT THE HELL
HAPPENED HERE?

08:49.760 --> 08:51.962
AHH?

08:54.164 --> 08:55.666
OH--OH, MY GOD.

08:55.666 --> 08:58.138
WE--WE NEED TO CALL
AN AMBULANCE.

08:58.138 --> 09:01.141
NO, SAM. IT'S OK.
THERE'S NO POINT.

09:01.141 --> 09:02.542
HE'S DEAD ALREADY.

09:02.542 --> 09:05.175
YOU KNOW, ONE DAY
YOU'RE COMING HOME,
HAPPY AS A CLAM,

09:05.175 --> 09:08.218
AND THEN BOOM,
YOU'RE GONE.

09:08.218 --> 09:09.950
THAT'S THE WAY
LIFE IS SAM.

09:09.950 --> 09:12.122
YOU'VE GOT TO EAT YOUR
APPLES WHILE YOU CAN.

09:12.122 --> 09:14.324
SO, LET ME GUESS,
AN ESCAPED SOUL
FROM HELL DID THIS.

09:14.324 --> 09:17.287
THAT'S VERY GOOD.
YOU'RE STARTING
TO CATCH ON TO THIS.

09:17.287 --> 09:18.929
BUT YOU KNOW WHAT
THE FUNNY THING IS?

09:18.929 --> 09:23.063
THE CORONER'S GONNA
BLAME THIS GUY'S DEATH
ON THE CAR CRASH.

09:23.063 --> 09:24.595
THE TRUTH?

09:24.595 --> 09:28.068
THIS FELLOW DIED
WHILE THE CAR
WAS STILL MOVING.

09:28.068 --> 09:29.840
HOW?

09:29.840 --> 09:30.941
WHO KNOWS?

09:30.941 --> 09:34.705
IT'S LIKE...MAGIC.

09:34.975 --> 09:36.947
OK, SO WHERE'S THE SOUL?

09:36.947 --> 09:37.708
I'M NOT GOOGLE, SAM.

09:37.708 --> 09:40.150
WELL, DON'T YOU HAVE
MINIONS DOWN IN HELL
KEEP TRACK OF THESE THINGS,

09:40.150 --> 09:42.613
LIKE WHO'S ESCAPED RECENTLY?
I DON'T KNOW HOW IT WORKS.
COME ON.

09:42.613 --> 09:45.155
MINIONS. YOU KNOW
WHO WORKS FOR ME
IN MY CENTRAL OFFICE?

09:45.155 --> 09:46.717
WHITE-COLLAR CRIMINALS.

09:46.717 --> 09:48.719
THEY HATE ME.
THEY HATE THEIR JOBS.

09:48.719 --> 09:51.321
I'M LUCKY IF I GET
COFFEE IN THE MORNING.

09:51.321 --> 09:53.593
[SCOFFS]

09:53.593 --> 09:54.925
OH...

09:54.925 --> 09:56.066
OK.

09:56.066 --> 09:57.127
I'LL HELP YOU.

09:57.127 --> 09:59.199
I REMEMBER THE FILE.

09:59.199 --> 10:02.903
IN LIFE, THE SOUL'S
NAME WAS BELLIFIORE.

10:02.903 --> 10:04.675
THAT'S IT?

10:04.675 --> 10:07.037
THAT--THAT'S NOT GONNA
HELP ME FIND HIM NOW.

10:07.037 --> 10:07.708
THIS COULD TAKE FOREVER.

10:07.708 --> 10:10.240
WELL, SINCE WHEN
ARE YOU IN SUCH A HURRY
TO CATCH SOULS FOR ME?

10:10.240 --> 10:13.013
BECAUSE I--I CARE
ABOUT THESE PEOPLE.

10:13.013 --> 10:14.044
I MEAN,
LOOK AT THIS GUY.

10:14.044 --> 10:17.648
ARE YOU SURE
IT'S NOT BECAUSE YOU
HAVE SOME OTHER PLANS?

10:17.648 --> 10:19.019
PLANS TO...

10:19.019 --> 10:21.251
LOCK LIPS
WITH SOMEBODY?

10:21.251 --> 10:22.953
FLAMING LIPS?

10:22.953 --> 10:24.154
LOOK, LOOK, I JUST--

10:24.154 --> 10:26.096
THE CONCERT ISN'T
UNTIL THIS WEEKEND, OK?

10:26.096 --> 10:29.099
AND I JUST--I FIGURED
IF I COULD TAKE
THE SOUL DOWN FAST,

10:29.099 --> 10:30.400
THEN I COULD STILL GO,
YOU KNOW?

10:30.400 --> 10:32.102
A LITTLE VACATION
FOR A JOB WELL DONE.

10:32.102 --> 10:34.905
AH. WELL,
HERE'S THE THING
ABOUT THAT, SAMMY.

10:34.905 --> 10:38.008
WHEN YOUR PARENTS
SIGNED THE CONTRACT
FOR YOUR SOUL,

10:38.008 --> 10:40.370
THEY DIDN'T THINK TO ASK
ABOUT VACATION DAYS,

10:40.370 --> 10:41.271
SO YOU DON'T GET THEM.

10:41.271 --> 10:43.974
SO THAT'S IT?
I WORK FOR YOU
FOR THE REST OF MY LIFE?

10:43.974 --> 10:44.875
NO VACATION, NOTHING?

10:44.875 --> 10:48.278
YEAH. AND I'M AFRAID
I WON'T BUDGE ON THIS.

10:48.278 --> 10:49.950
SETS A BAD PRECEDENT.

10:49.950 --> 10:51.752
GOD, YOU SOUND LIKE TED.

10:51.752 --> 10:54.054
OHH, THAT WAS HARSH.

10:54.054 --> 10:55.886
TED IS A REAL
DOUCHE BAG.

10:55.886 --> 10:57.427
YEAH, WELL,
THE TRUTH HURTS.

10:57.427 --> 10:58.929
YOU PUSH ME AROUND,
YOU KNOW.

10:58.929 --> 11:01.361
YOU MAKE UP THESE
TOTALLY ARBITRARY RULES

11:01.361 --> 11:04.134
AND EXPECT ME TO JUST
BE YOUR LITTLE ROBOT?

11:04.134 --> 11:05.065
NO! I'M SORRY, OK?

11:05.065 --> 11:07.938
I REFUSE
TO ACCEPT YOUR POWER
OVER ME, ALL RIGHT?

11:07.938 --> 11:09.970
I'M NOT YOUR MACHINE.

11:12.843 --> 11:15.045
[TRUCK HORN HONKS]

11:24.214 --> 11:26.056
[GRUNTS]

11:28.688 --> 11:31.792
I TRUST
I'VE MADE MY POINT.

11:31.792 --> 11:34.825
LOUD AND CLEAR.

11:34.825 --> 11:36.727
HEH.

11:48.038 --> 11:49.940
[BOX SHUDDERS]

11:49.940 --> 11:50.941
WHAT IS IN
THAT THING?

11:50.941 --> 11:53.113
Sam: WHATEVER IT IS,
IT WAS FORGED IN HELL.

11:53.113 --> 11:57.017
SOCK, YOU REALLY THINK
THAT'S GONNA HELP YOU
SLOW IT DOWN?

11:57.017 --> 11:59.119
BEN, YOU WANT TO TRADE?
NO.

11:59.119 --> 12:00.891
[BOX SHUDDERS]

12:00.891 --> 12:02.893
[WHISPERS] OK.

12:04.354 --> 12:05.195
I'M GOING IN.

12:05.195 --> 12:07.027
[SOCK WHISPERING]
All right, get it.

12:07.027 --> 12:08.428
I'M GOING IN.
Ben: NICE AND EASY.

12:08.428 --> 12:12.102
I'M GONNA DO IT.
NICE AND EASY.

12:13.133 --> 12:16.006
[BOX RATTLING]

12:20.871 --> 12:23.914
[COOING]

12:25.015 --> 12:26.416
AW.

12:26.416 --> 12:28.148
HE'S CUTE!

12:28.148 --> 12:29.419
[COOING]

12:29.419 --> 12:30.750
HEH!

12:30.750 --> 12:31.822
HEY.

12:31.822 --> 12:33.223
Sock: AW, PRETTY BIRD.

12:33.223 --> 12:35.285
ALL RIGHT, SO WE HAVE
THE VESSEL,

12:35.285 --> 12:36.927
BUT ALL WE KNOW
ABOUT THE SOUL

12:36.927 --> 12:39.229
IS THAT HIS NAME
WAS BELLIFIORE...

12:39.229 --> 12:42.062
WHEN HE WAS ALIVE. OK.

12:42.062 --> 12:43.363
812 HITS? HA HA!

12:43.363 --> 12:45.866
ALL RIGHT, WE GOTTA
NARROW THIS DOWN A LITTLE.

12:45.866 --> 12:47.097
MM-HMM. HOW?

12:47.097 --> 12:50.240
BELLIFIORE, SOUL.

12:50.240 --> 12:51.942
NOPE. OK.

12:51.942 --> 12:53.343
BELLIFIORE, EVIL.

12:53.343 --> 12:55.075
PLUS EVIL.

12:55.075 --> 12:56.907
SOCK...

12:57.477 --> 12:58.809
NOW THE MOUSE
HAS DISAPPEARED!

12:58.809 --> 13:01.781
I SWEAR, THE DEVIL
DOESN'T EVEN WANT ME
TO SOLVE THIS.

13:01.781 --> 13:03.413
GUYS?
Ted: SAM?

13:03.413 --> 13:06.056
DO I HEAR UNAUTHORIZED
CHIT-CHAT?

13:06.056 --> 13:07.287
UH...UH-UH.

13:07.287 --> 13:11.121
WHAT, ARE YOU TALKING
TO YOURSELF AGAIN, SAM?

13:11.461 --> 13:14.825
THAT IS A SAD, SAD
STATE OF AFFAIRS, MY FRIEND.

13:14.825 --> 13:17.427
BECAUSE NO ONE ANSWERS.

13:17.427 --> 13:19.299
EVER.

13:22.032 --> 13:24.034
AS YOU WERE.

13:25.976 --> 13:28.478
GOD, I THOUGHT YOU GUYS
DISAPPEARED, TOO.

13:28.478 --> 13:30.040
AH.

13:30.040 --> 13:31.811
THIS POWER'S STUPID, SAM.

13:31.811 --> 13:35.185
IF MAKING THINGS DISAPPEAR
IS SUPPOSED TO BE A CLUE,

13:35.185 --> 13:36.516
I DON'T GET IT.

13:36.516 --> 13:38.348
WAIT, WAIT, THAT'S GOOD!

13:38.348 --> 13:40.250
DISAPPEAR. HOLD ON.

13:40.250 --> 13:42.352
BELLIFIORE, DISAPPEAR.

13:42.352 --> 13:44.294
YES! ALL RIGHT.
GOOD JOB.

13:44.294 --> 13:47.427
ENRICO BELLIFIORE
WAS A MAGICIAN
IN THE 1920s.

13:47.427 --> 13:47.998
NEVER HEAD OF HIM.

13:47.998 --> 13:52.262
HE'S FEATURED
ON A DOCUMENTARY DVD
DARK SIDE OF MAGIC.

13:52.262 --> 13:55.535
LET'S FIND THAT.
MAYBE...COME ON.

13:55.535 --> 13:57.107
THERE'S 2 COPIES
IN STORE RIGHT NOW.

13:57.107 --> 14:00.840
MM. GOD BLESS YOU,
WORKBENCH.
YOU HAVE EVERYTHING.

14:00.840 --> 14:02.842
Sam: AWESOME.

14:06.516 --> 14:07.617
HOW MUCH
FOR THE FLAT SCREEN?

14:07.617 --> 14:10.981
UH, A MILLION DOLLARS.
TRY BEST BUY.

14:12.052 --> 14:14.024
Narrator: DATELINE 1929.

14:14.024 --> 14:16.426
FORMER STAGE MAGICIAN
ENRICO BELLIFIORE

14:16.426 --> 14:18.058
WALKS THE LAST MILE
FOR MURDER.

14:18.058 --> 14:21.531
A YOUNG WAITER
WITH DREAMS OF BECOMING
THE NEXT HOUDINI,

14:21.531 --> 14:24.294
BELLIFIORE TRADED IN
HIS BREADSTICKS

14:24.294 --> 14:26.036
FOR MAGIC TRICKS.

14:26.036 --> 14:27.067
THE UNADORING MASSES

14:27.067 --> 14:29.569
FELT BELLIFIORE NEEDED
TO SHARPEN HIS SKILLS.

14:29.569 --> 14:32.202
WHAT? I SAW WIRES.
DID YOU GUYS SEE WIRES?

14:32.202 --> 14:33.273
Ben: YEAH.

14:33.273 --> 14:34.104
AND SO DID THE THEATER,

14:34.104 --> 14:35.445
SO BELLIFIORE TOOK
ONE LAST STAB AT FAME,

14:35.445 --> 14:40.210
AND THE CROWDS
LINED UP TO SEE
THIS MALEVOLENT MAGICIAN

14:40.210 --> 14:42.382
PERFORM HIS FINAL
ROPE TRICK.

14:42.382 --> 14:45.255
AND THIS HAS BEEN ANOTHER
EDITION OF MOVIE-VUE NEWS.

14:45.255 --> 14:47.117
OK. ALL RIGHT.
THAT'S NEWS WITH A VIEW!

14:47.117 --> 14:49.289
NOW WE KNOW
WHO BELLIFIORE WAS
WHEN HE WAS ALIVE.

14:49.289 --> 14:51.461
WE JUST NEED TO FIGURE
OUT WHERE HE IS NOW.

14:51.461 --> 14:51.992
YEAH.

14:51.992 --> 14:54.294
Andi on P.A.: SAM OLIVER
FOR CARRY OUT, REGISTER 2.

14:54.294 --> 14:56.396
SAM OLIVER, REGISTER 2.
THAT'S ANDI.

14:56.396 --> 14:58.128
YOU GONNA TELL HER
YOU CAN'T GO TO THE CONCERT?

14:58.128 --> 14:59.269
DON'T REALLY
HAVE A CHOICE.

14:59.269 --> 15:01.101
THE DEVIL MADE IT
PRETTY CLEAR.

15:01.101 --> 15:01.501
YEAH.

15:01.501 --> 15:04.004
Andi: I NEED TO TALK TO YOU
ABOUT THE CONCERT.

15:04.004 --> 15:06.106
OH, YEAH. I...

15:06.106 --> 15:07.037
I COULD ONLY GET
2 TICKETS.

15:07.037 --> 15:10.110
OH, WELL, THEN JUST--
UH, MAYBE GO WITH JOSIE.

15:10.110 --> 15:14.184
WELL, I MEAN,
IN ALL FAIRNESS,
I DID ASK YOU FIRST.

15:14.184 --> 15:16.216
YOU'RE--WAIT, YEAH.

15:16.216 --> 15:19.019
BUT, WHAT, SO JUST
YOU AND ME TOGETHER?

15:19.019 --> 15:22.552
YEAH.
WHAT'S THE BIG DEAL?

15:23.293 --> 15:26.256
WELL, WHERE WOULD--
WHERE WOULD WE SLEEP?

15:26.256 --> 15:27.257
MY CAR.

15:27.257 --> 15:28.598
IT'LL BE TIGHT, BUT...

15:28.598 --> 15:30.660
WELL, I MEAN,
IF YOU'RE NOT UP FOR IT,

15:30.660 --> 15:32.002
THEN I COMPLETELY
UNDERSTAND.

15:32.002 --> 15:34.965
NO, NO, NO! I'M UP FOR IT!
I'M COMPLETELY UP FOR IT.

15:34.965 --> 15:36.666
VERY, VERY UP. I--

15:36.666 --> 15:37.607
WELL, GREAT.

15:37.607 --> 15:40.410
ALL RIGHT, YEAH.
THAT SOUNDS GREAT.

15:40.971 --> 15:42.112
AHEM.

15:42.112 --> 15:43.643
OH. YOU GOT IT
FROM HERE?

15:43.643 --> 15:45.145
OH. YES, YES.

15:45.145 --> 15:46.076
SAM!

15:46.076 --> 15:48.718
SORRY. I GOT IT.
I GOT IT.

15:51.021 --> 15:52.082
AHH.

15:52.082 --> 15:52.582
[GIGGLES]

15:52.582 --> 15:55.255
Woman: NORA,
DON'T THROW FOOD.

15:55.255 --> 15:56.156
HEH HEH.

15:56.156 --> 15:59.329
IT'S OK.
IT--IT HAPPENS.

15:59.329 --> 15:59.990
UH...

15:59.990 --> 16:04.694
EXCUSE ME, MA'AM.
WHERE--WHERE DID YOU
FIND ALL THESE APPLES?

16:05.335 --> 16:06.436
Ben: I'M CONFUSED.

16:06.436 --> 16:09.599
YOU AND ANDI ARE GOING TO
THE CONCERT ALONE OVERNIGHT.

16:09.599 --> 16:10.340
THAT'S RIGHT.

16:10.340 --> 16:12.572
WELL, WHAT ABOUT THE DEVIL
SAYING NO VACATION TIME?

16:12.572 --> 16:15.605
BEN, WE'RE TALKING ABOUT
ME AND ANDI ALONE OVERNIGHT.

16:15.605 --> 16:18.078
COME ON, THIS IS MY SHOT.
I HAVE TO TAKE IT.

16:18.078 --> 16:19.479
OK, BUT WHAT ABOUT
THE DEVIL?

16:19.479 --> 16:23.183
I'M CHOOSING TO NOT
THINK ABOUT THAT RIGHT NOW.

16:23.183 --> 16:24.514
OH, REALLY.

16:24.514 --> 16:27.717
HEY, LOOK AT THAT SWORD.
THAT'S GOT TO BE OUR GUY.

16:27.717 --> 16:28.458
Sock: HMM.

16:28.458 --> 16:30.160
YOU KNOW, MAYBE IF
WE CATCH HIM FAST,

16:30.160 --> 16:31.991
THE DEVIL MIGHT LET ME
GO TO THE CONCERT WITH ANDI.

16:31.991 --> 16:33.393
YEAH, 'CAUSE HE'S
A REAL PEACH LIKE THAT.

16:33.393 --> 16:37.427
SO THEN WE POINT
THE BIRDCAGE AT THE SOUL
AND OPEN THE DOOR.

16:37.427 --> 16:37.997
I GUESS.

16:37.997 --> 16:39.569
NOT LIKE THERE'S ANY
MOVING PARTS.

16:39.569 --> 16:41.031
WHEN DOES THE BIRD
COME IN?

16:41.031 --> 16:41.731
MAYBE HE'S BAIT.

16:41.731 --> 16:45.135
WAIT, I'M SORRY, BAIT?
NOBODY'S HURTING WINSTON.

16:45.135 --> 16:46.406
WHO'S WINSTON?

16:46.406 --> 16:47.477
THE BIRD.

16:47.477 --> 16:50.110
YOU NAMED
THE VESSEL?

16:50.110 --> 16:52.642
DUDE, WINSTON IS NOT
A BIRD'S NAME, BEN.

16:52.642 --> 16:55.215
OK, WELL,
YOU TELL ME WHAT
A BIRD'S NAME IS.

16:55.215 --> 16:58.318
I DON'T KNOW.
UH, HOW ABOUT FLAPPY OR PAUL.

16:58.318 --> 17:01.091
WHA--NO, NO,
HE'S A WINSTON.

17:01.091 --> 17:02.122
RIGHT, WINSTON?

17:02.122 --> 17:03.423
WHAT IS WRONG
WITH YOU?

17:03.423 --> 17:04.494
MY DAD'S SUPER ALLERGIC.

17:04.494 --> 17:06.426
YOU KNOW, I COULDN'T
HAVE ANY PETS,

17:06.426 --> 17:08.428
SO THIS LITTLE GUY
FILLS THAT VOID.

17:08.428 --> 17:11.601
YOU SAID I FILLED
THAT VOID, BEN.

17:12.132 --> 17:15.034
[INDISTINCT WHISPERING]

17:15.034 --> 17:17.407
Sock: OH, MY GOD.
LOOK AT THIS TOOLBOX.

17:17.407 --> 17:20.110
IS THAT ALL I HAVE TO DO
IS SLAP ON
A LITTLE GUYLINER,

17:20.110 --> 17:22.142
I GET TO SHOWER
WITH CAMERON DIAZ?

17:22.142 --> 17:23.173
UH, PROBABLY NOT.

17:23.173 --> 17:23.813
WELL, IT'S HER LOSS.

17:23.813 --> 17:25.645
Ben: SHE WOULDN'T THINK SO.

17:25.645 --> 17:28.618
[SOCK WHISPERING]
Sorry, sorry.

17:35.625 --> 17:36.226
Sam: OHH.

17:36.226 --> 17:37.787
HOW'S HE DO THAT
WITH THE SWORD?

17:37.787 --> 17:40.830
HE'S AN ESCAPED SOUL.
IT COULD BE REAL MAGIC.

17:40.830 --> 17:43.393
YOU GUYS WANT TO SEE
SOME REAL MAGIC?

17:43.393 --> 17:45.635
CHECK THIS OUT.

17:47.637 --> 17:49.269
IT'S GONE.

17:49.269 --> 17:51.171
WHERE'D IT GO?

17:51.171 --> 17:53.103
[WHISPERS] Wow.

17:53.443 --> 17:55.145
WHAT ARE WE
WAITING FOR?

17:55.145 --> 17:56.776
WE CAN'T
JUST SUCK HIM IN

17:56.776 --> 17:58.108
WITH ALL THESE
PEOPLE ROUND.

17:58.108 --> 18:00.580
LET'S JUST CATCH HIM
AFTER THE SHOW.

18:02.512 --> 18:05.655
[APPLAUSE]

18:07.086 --> 18:08.087
SO THAT'S IT?

18:08.087 --> 18:11.191
WHAT, NO CHEERING?
NO STANDING OVATION?

18:11.191 --> 18:13.663
HEH.

18:14.794 --> 18:16.426
IT'S NOT FUNNY.

18:16.426 --> 18:19.098
I PERFORM MAGIC
NO ONE ELSE CAN TOUCH,

18:19.098 --> 18:21.131
AND ALL YOU DO
IS JUST SIT THERE.

18:21.131 --> 18:23.503
WHAT DO YOU PEOPLE WANT?

18:23.503 --> 18:25.505
MAYBE YOU NEED PROOF--

18:25.505 --> 18:28.178
PROOF THAT I'M THE GREATEST
MAGICIAN IN THE WORLD.

18:28.178 --> 18:30.140
WHAT'S THE MATTER, MATE?

18:30.140 --> 18:31.811
DON'T YOU LIKE MY SHOW?

18:31.811 --> 18:33.483
I'M JUST HEADED
TO THE RESTROOM.

18:33.483 --> 18:35.545
AND THAT'S BETTER
THAN MY ACT?

18:35.545 --> 18:38.418
YOU'RE A MAGICIAN
AT A FOOD FESTIVAL.

18:38.418 --> 18:39.649
WHAT--WHAT DO YOU WANT
FROM ME?

18:39.649 --> 18:41.751
COME ON, WHY DON'T
YOU GET UP ON STAGE

18:41.751 --> 18:43.793
FOR A TRICK GUARANTEED
TO IMPRESS YOU?

18:43.793 --> 18:44.524
TO IMPRESS ALL OF YOU?

18:44.524 --> 18:48.198
COME ON, EVERYBODY,
A ROUND OF APPLAUSE
TO ENCOURAGE THIS GUY.

18:48.198 --> 18:49.659
COME ON, COME ON.

18:49.659 --> 18:50.830
[WHISTLING]

18:50.830 --> 18:53.403
IS THIS A REAL SWORD?

18:55.765 --> 18:57.907
Man: IT'S REAL.

18:57.907 --> 19:01.211
YOU BETTER BELIEVE IT.

19:02.372 --> 19:03.343
UNH!

19:03.343 --> 19:05.315
OH!
OH!

19:05.315 --> 19:07.517
[GRUNTING]

19:08.918 --> 19:12.452
[APPLAUSE]

19:17.657 --> 19:19.589
YOU GOTTA ADMIT THAT WAS
A PRETTY GOOD TRICK.

19:19.589 --> 19:21.331
Sam: LET'S CATCH HIM
BACKSTAGE.

19:21.331 --> 19:22.932
YEAH, YEAH.
I WANT AN AUTOGRAPH.

19:22.932 --> 19:26.236
HEY, I WAITED
OUT FRONT TILL
THE LOBBY WAS EMPTY.

19:26.236 --> 19:26.866
NO SIGN OF HIM.

19:26.866 --> 19:28.898
YEAH, AND HE DIDN'T
PASS ME OUT BACK.

19:28.898 --> 19:32.702
DAMN IT, WE LOST HIM.
[SIGHS]

19:33.803 --> 19:36.246
Sam: ALL RIGHT, IT SUCKS
THE SOUL GOT AWAY,

19:36.246 --> 19:37.347
BUT AT LEAST
NOBODY DIED, RIGHT?

19:37.347 --> 19:39.649
Ben: YEAH,
AND NOTHING HAPPENED
TO WINSTON.

19:39.649 --> 19:40.680
AND NOBODY DIED, TOO.

19:40.680 --> 19:43.182
Sam: WHOA.
Sock: WHOA, WHAT HAPPENED?

19:43.182 --> 19:44.183
[POLICE RADIO CHATTER]

19:44.183 --> 19:46.616
EXCUSE ME.
UH, WHAT HAPPENED TO HIM?

19:46.616 --> 19:48.718
Paramedic: OH,
WE FOUND HIM KEELED OVER,

19:48.718 --> 19:50.620
MASSIVE INTERNAL INJURIES.

19:50.620 --> 19:53.823
MUST HAVE BEEN
HIT BY A CAR OR SOMETHING.

20:12.482 --> 20:13.483
ANOTHER BEER, PLEASE.

20:13.483 --> 20:15.985
YOU KNOW, I'VE NEVER SEEN
A DEAD BODY UP CLOSE BEFORE.

20:15.985 --> 20:17.947
IT'S MESSED UP.

20:17.947 --> 20:18.488
I KNOW, RIGHT?

20:18.488 --> 20:21.591
I MEAN YOU'D THINK
THAT SEEING SCARFACE
ALL THOSE TIMES,

20:21.591 --> 20:23.653
I'D BE BETTER PREPARED
FOR THAT, BUT...

20:23.653 --> 20:25.625
WHY'D THE MAGICIAN
KILL THAT GUY?

20:25.625 --> 20:27.557
I DON'T KNOW.
I FEEL LIKE
HE HATES THE AUDIENCE.

20:27.557 --> 20:30.860
LIKE HE BLAMES THEM
FOR HIS CRAPPY CAREER
WHEN HE WAS ALIVE.

20:30.860 --> 20:34.003
WELL, AT LEAST WE KNOW
WHERE HE'S GONNA BE.

20:34.003 --> 20:36.336
THE NEXT PERFORMANCE
IS TOMORROW AT NOON,

20:36.336 --> 20:38.908
WHICH MEANS WE NEED
TO ASK TED FOR TIME OFF.

20:38.908 --> 20:40.440
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
NOTHING.

20:40.440 --> 20:42.572
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
NOTHING!

20:42.572 --> 20:44.744
LET ME...

20:45.615 --> 20:46.616
YOU NEED HELP.

20:46.616 --> 20:48.318
I'M WORRIED ABOUT WINSTON.

20:48.318 --> 20:49.919
HE'S INNOCENT IN ALL THIS.

20:49.919 --> 20:50.920
WHAT ABOUT ME, MAN?
I'M AN INNOCENT.

20:50.920 --> 20:54.023
YOU'RE NOT FEEDING ME
PRETZELS AND NESTLING ME
TO YOUR BREAST.

20:54.023 --> 20:54.984
OK, THAT'S JUST GROSS.

20:54.984 --> 20:57.757
BECAUSE
YOU SIGNED A CONTRACT
WITH THE DEVIL, SAM.

20:57.757 --> 21:00.259
NO, I DID NOT.
YOU DIDN'T SIGN ANYTHING?

21:00.259 --> 21:01.961
NO. NO, MY PARENTS DID.

21:01.961 --> 21:02.532
THAT'S WEIRD.

21:02.532 --> 21:04.694
SAYS THE GUY
WITH THE SHIRT FULL OF BIRD.

21:04.694 --> 21:07.297
DUDE, YOU SHOULD
REALLY TAKE A LOOK
AT THAT CONTRACT.

21:07.297 --> 21:09.569
THAT'S NOT COOL
YOUR PARENTS SOLD YOUR SOUL

21:09.569 --> 21:10.970
TO THE DEVIL
WITHOUT YOUR CONSENT.

21:10.970 --> 21:13.873
ISN'T THAT RIGHT,
LITTLE MAN?

21:13.873 --> 21:15.945
Sam: YEAH,
THAT'S A GOOD POINT.

21:15.945 --> 21:20.650
SEE IF MY PARENTS
HAVE A COPY OF
THE CONTRACT SOMEWHERE.

21:21.311 --> 21:23.853
HEY, GOOD MORNING.
YOU'RE UP EARLY.

21:23.853 --> 21:25.815
YEAH. HEY.

21:25.815 --> 21:27.987
UM...

21:27.987 --> 21:30.990
CAN I SEE MY CONTRACT?

21:30.990 --> 21:32.962
WHICH CONTRACT IS THAT?

21:32.962 --> 21:35.425
UH...IT'S...

21:35.425 --> 21:37.066
THE CONTRACT.

21:37.066 --> 21:40.900
YOU KNOW,
FOR MY SOUL?

21:41.701 --> 21:43.503
WHAT DO YOU WANT
TO SEE THAT FOR?

21:43.503 --> 21:46.536
WELL, I JUST THOUGHT
I SHOULD SEE IT.

21:46.536 --> 21:47.907
YOU KNOW WHAT?

21:47.907 --> 21:49.839
YOU'RE RIGHT.

21:49.839 --> 21:51.941
YOU DESERVE TO SEE IT.

21:52.912 --> 21:54.644
OK, UH, LET ME THINK.

21:54.644 --> 21:56.486
WHERE DID WE PUT THAT?

21:56.486 --> 21:58.388
Sam: WELL,
WHAT'S IN THERE?

21:58.388 --> 22:00.990
THIS IS YOUR
MEMENTO BOX.

22:00.990 --> 22:05.955
I HAVEN'T LOOKED
IN HERE IN YEARS.

22:05.955 --> 22:07.697
HEH HEH.

22:07.697 --> 22:09.899
YOU PUT THE CONTRACT
FOR MY SOUL

22:09.899 --> 22:14.404
WITH MY THIRD-GRADE
REPORT CARD
AND MR. HUGGLES?

22:14.404 --> 22:15.835
YEAH, YOU'RE RIGHT.

22:15.835 --> 22:17.367
IT'S NOT GONNA BE IN HERE.

22:17.367 --> 22:21.040
OK, MAYBE YOUR DAD
KNOWS WHERE IT IS.

22:23.042 --> 22:26.015
[CELL PHONE DIALING]

22:26.015 --> 22:27.076
OH. WELL, UH...

22:27.076 --> 22:29.348
DID YOU CHECK
THE LINEN CLOSET?

22:29.348 --> 22:30.420
YES. JOHN, YOU KNOW,

22:30.420 --> 22:33.823
I DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHY YOU CAN'T GET
A HANDLE ON THE PAPERWORK.

22:33.823 --> 22:35.455
WE HAVE ABSOLUTELY NO
FILING SYSTEM.

22:35.455 --> 22:37.627
YOU KEEP YOUR GOLF CLEATS
AND TENNIS SHOES...

22:37.627 --> 22:38.728
YOU'RE UP, JOHN.

22:38.728 --> 22:40.960
CAN WE TALK
ABOUT THIS LATER?

22:40.960 --> 22:41.931
FINE.

22:41.931 --> 22:44.534
BUT THAT'S YOUR ANSWER
TO EVERYTHING.

22:44.534 --> 22:45.935
JUST...UH...

22:45.935 --> 22:48.938
CHECK THE OFFICE
WITH THE TAX RETURNS.

22:48.938 --> 22:50.470
OK.

22:50.470 --> 22:52.542
